dc_title_s: Partie de l'Amérique septentrionale, qui comprend le cours de l'Ohio, la Nlle. Angleterre, la Nlle York, le New Jersey, la Pensylvanie, le Maryland, la Virginie, la Caroline
dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. "Avec privilège 1755." Title on verso: "Cours de l'Ohyo." Covers the area from the Great Lakes to South Carolina and from the Atlantic coast to the Mississippi River. Shows provinces, counties, towns and cities, riviers, Indian villages and tribal territory, forts, numerous place-names, and relief. Appears in the author's Atlas universal. 1757 [i.e. 1758]. Includes "Supplément pour la Caroline." Historic Maps copies 2 and 4 lack title on verso.
